{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:first-corinthians.12",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 12,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 12 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:1",
      "text": "Now concerning spiritual things, brothers, I don’ t want you to be ignorant.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:2",
      "text": "You know that when you were heathen, you were led away to those mute idols, however you might be led.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:3",
      "text": "Therefore I make known to you that no man speaking by God ’ s Spirit says, “ Jesus is accursed.” No one can say, “ Jesus is Lord,” but by the Holy Spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:4",
      "text": "Now there are various kinds of gifts, but the same Spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:5",
      "text": "There are various kinds of service, and the same Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:6",
      "text": "There are various kinds of workings, but the same God who works all things in all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:7",
      "text": "But to each one is given the manifestation of the Spirit for the profit of all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:8",
      "text": "For to one is given through the Spirit the word of wisdom, and to another the word of knowledge according to the same Spirit,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:9",
      "text": "to another faith by the same Spirit, and to another gifts of healings by the same Spirit,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:10",
      "text": "and to another workings of miracles, and to another prophecy, and to another discerning of spirits, to another different kinds of languages, and to another the interpretation of languages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:11",
      "text": "But the one and the same Spirit produces all of these, distributing to each one separately as he desires.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:12",
      "text": "For as the body is one and has many members, and all the members of the body, being many, are one body; so also is Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:13",
      "text": "For in one Spirit we were all baptized into one body, whether Jews or Greeks, whether bond or free; and were all given to drink into one Spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:14",
      "text": "For the body is not one member, but many.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:15",
      "text": "If the foot would say, “ Because I ’m not the hand, I ’m not part of the body,” it is not therefore not part of the body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:16",
      "text": "If the ear would say, “ Because I ’m not the eye, I ’m not part of the body,” it ’s not therefore not part of the body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:17",
      "text": "If the whole body were an eye, where would the hearing be? If the whole were hearing, where would the smelling be?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:18",
      "text": "But now God has set the members, each one of them, in the body, just as he desired.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:19",
      "text": "If they were all one member, where would the body be?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:20",
      "text": "But now they are many members, but one body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:21",
      "text": "The eye can ’ t tell the hand, “ I have no need for you,” or again the head to the feet, “ I have no need for you.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:22",
      "text": "No, much rather, those members of the body which seem to be weaker are necessary.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:23",
      "text": "Those parts of the body which we think to be less honorable, on those we bestow more abundant honor; and our unpresentable parts have more abundant modesty,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:24",
      "text": "while our presentable parts have no such need. But God composed the body together, giving more abundant honor to the inferior part,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:25",
      "text": "that there should be no division in the body, but that the members should have the same care for one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:26",
      "text": "When one member suffers, all the members suffer with it. When one member is honored, all the members rejoice with it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:27",
      "text": "Now you are the body of Christ, and members individually.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:28",
      "text": "God has set some in the assembly: first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then miracle workers, then gifts of healings, helps, governments, and various kinds of languages.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:29",
      "text": "Are all apostles? Are all prophets? Are all teachers? Are all miracle workers?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:30",
      "text": "Do all have gifts of healings? Do all speak with various languages? Do all interpret?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.12.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 12:31",
      "text": "But earnestly desire the best gifts. Moreover, I show a most excellent way to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
